AntiAliasingFilter: Prior to analog-to-digital conversion, an anti-aliasing filter is used to remove any frequency components above half the sampling rate (Nyquist frequency) to prevent aliasing. This filter needs to be a low-pass filter with a cutoff frequency set appropriately based on the ADC's sampling rate.

ADC: The analog-to-digital converter provides the means to digitize the conditioned analog signal for further digital processing, storage, or digital display. The sampling rate must be at least twice the highest frequency of interest (according to the Nyquist-Shannon sampling theorem).
